Package pl.edu.agh.kis.pz1.model

Class Hotel

java.lang.Object
pl.edu.agh.kis.pz1.model.Hotel
public class Hotel extends Object
The Hotel class represents a hotel with a specific number of floors and rooms. It maintains a map of room numbers to Room objects.

      public Hotel()
      Default constructor for the Hotel class. Initializes the hotel with zero floors, zero rooms, and no room mappings. - floorsCount: Initially set to 0, indicating no floors are defined. - roomsCount: Initially set to 0, indicating no rooms are defined. - rooms: Initially set empty, indicating no room data or structure has been assigned.

    • addRoom

      public void addRoom(Room room)
      Adds a new room to the hotel. If a room with the same number already exists, the method does nothing. The room is added to the map of rooms, and the total count of rooms is incremented. Additionally, the total number of floors (floorsCount) is updated if the new room is on a higher floor.
      Parameters:
      room - The room to be added to the hotel.
